---
import banner from "@/src/assets/images/banners/Emerging_Tech_Banner.png";
import PageLayout from "@/src/layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import jcTechsStreetDetection from "@/src/assets/images/ai/jc-techs-street-detection.png";
import jcTechsLogo from "@/src/assets/images/ai/logos/JC-Techs-logo.jpg";

const keywords = [
  "Scalable AI",
  "Complete Streets Data",
  "Dash Cams",
  "Computer Vision",
  "JC-Techs Corp.",
  "Artificial Intelligence",
  "Street Infrastructure"
];

const description =
  "Scalable and Sustainable AI Solutions for Complete Streets Data Creation and Maintenance with Off-the-shelf Dash Cams - AI project by JC-Techs Corp.";
---

<PageLayout title="Scalable AI Solutions for Complete Streets Data" bannerImage={banner} keywords={keywords} description={description}>
  <Fragment slot="banner">Artificial Intelligence</Fragment>
  <main>
    <div class="page-header">
      <h2>Scalable and Sustainable AI Solutions for Complete Streets Data Creation and Maintenance with Off-the-shelf Dash Cams</h2>
      <Image src={jcTechsLogo} alt="JC-Techs Corp. logo" class="page-logo" />
    </div>
    <p class="company-attribution">By: JC-Techs Corp.</p>
    
    <div class="row mt-5">
      <div class="col-12">
        <section class="mb-5">
          <h3 class="blue">Project Objective & Overview</h3>
          <p>
            The objective of the project is to develop computer vision-based AI technologies and systems for <strong>automatically digitizing and maintaining street infrastructure data by only utilizing standard dash cam street view footage</strong>. The company also delivered software tools for data verification.
          </p>
          <p>
            The goals of the system development is to provide <strong>verifiable, affordable, scalable, and sustainable solutions</strong> to address the following key challenges:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Incomplete data details in street infrastructure attributes.</li>
            <li>State or unreliable data due to lack of mechanisms for affordable, trusted, and continuous updates with sufficient groundings.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>Pilot site:</strong> Tacoma and Lakewood, WA
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-4">
      <div class="col-12">
        <section class="mb-5">
          <h3 class="blue">Key Results & Findings</h3>
          <div class="row align-items-start">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
              <p><strong>Technical approach:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li>To ensure that <strong>no need to manually watch the footage for miss-detected objects</strong>, our first technical goal is to successfully detect all the street objects of interest from the dashcam street view footage. We have <strong>achieved this zero-miss goal for traffic lights, road markings, parking signs, crosswalk, traffic signs, pedestrian lights, directional signs, and fire hydrants</strong>.</li>
                <li>Developed tracking and classification algorithms to remove the duplicate detected instances and the false positive instances and correctly categorize the detected street objects.</li>
                <li>Developed a cross-validation system (right figure) to ensure <strong>100% accurate data creation</strong>.</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                <strong>Key challenges:</strong>
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Object localization</li>
                <li>Unique object tracking</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                <strong>Opportunities identified:</strong>
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Automate road condition monitoring</li>
                <li>Asset data maintenance</li>
                <li>Parking inventory management</li>
                <li>Data validation with grounding</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5">
              <Image src={jcTechsStreetDetection} alt="JC-Techs street detection and validation interface" class="img-fluid my-4 rounded" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <section class="mb-5">
          <h3 class="blue">Company Info</h3>
          <p>
            JC-Techs is a University of Washington spin-off startup, founded by a team with strong AI and software expertise and a proven track record of securing grants and purchase orders from federal agencies and municipal governments. JC-Techs has obtained the purchase orders from Las Vegas, Bellevue, and San Francisco.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Project POC:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@jc-techs.com">contact@jc-techs.com</a><br/>
            <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.jc-techs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.jc-techs.com/</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <section class="mb-5">
          <h3 class="blue">Next Steps</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Dashcam footage fusion:</strong> city drives using rental vehicles with dashcams, integration with existing municipal fleets with dashcams, and continuous video feeds from commercial vehicle dashcams, which <strong>enable full city coverage within a one-month cycle</strong>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>Additional investments:</strong> Federal fundings and private investments
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>Commercialization plan:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Partner with private companies</strong> for data creation and maintenance and asset condition monitoring.</li>
            <li><strong>Data validation services</strong> for private partners and government agencies.</li>
            <li>Serve under resourced community to <strong>fill City agency workforce gaps</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .company-attribution {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #666;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }


  section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  section p {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: nowrap;
  }

  .page-header h2 {
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    min-width: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page-logo {
    width: 140px;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 70px;
    object-fit: contain;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-header {
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .page-logo {
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
